  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to assess performance and cost-effectiveness of rapid diagnostic
      test(RDT) aided malaria diagnosis versus symptom-based/clinical diagnosis in patients of all
      ages with reported fever last 48 hours alone in primary health care settings in Zanzibar.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
